  "body": "<!--ðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’Ž\r\n\r\nHellooo! ðŸ˜„ \r\n\r\nTo help us tend to your issue faster, please search our currently open issues before submitting a new one.\r\nExisting issues often contain information about workarounds, resolution, or progress updates.\r\n\r\nðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’Ž-->\r\n\r\n# ðŸš€ Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nPrysm has an api that list peers. The data it provides is however limited (multi-address and direction only ).\r\n\r\nThe request is to enhance the api and provide more fields from the peer store. Lighthouse has a similar interface that has a richer content.\r\n\r\nThis allows for better analysis of peers.\r\n\r\nThe above request was discussed already on discord between @nisdas and @protolambda\r\n![2020-06-15_13-43-31](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28559038/84655783-e0db6180-af11-11ea-8b0c-eedc33c18b91.png)\r\n\r\nThis is how the Lighthouse endpoint looks like:\r\n![2020-06-15_13-45-09](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28559038/84655826-f486c800-af11-11ea-999b-6d7765bc0bd6.png)\r\n\r\nThis is prysm currently (also no option for selecting a single peer):\r\n![2020-06-15_13-49-35](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28559038/84655888-108a6980-af12-11ea-9b26-9bb0a9c2213b.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\n<!-- âœï¸--> If you have a solution in mind, please describe it.\r\n\r\n### Describe alternatives you've considered\r\n\r\n<!-- âœï¸--> Have you considered any alternative solutions or workarounds?\r\n",
